text:
She's carved out a successful career in the fashion industry since being discovered by Tyra Banks.
And Winnie Harlow was showcasing her style credentials when she stepped out in West Hollywood on Tuesday night, partying at celebrity hotspot TAO.
The striking star put her long legs on display in a glamorous, thigh-skimming minidress with a subtle shimmer.

She dressed the spaghetti strap number down with an oversized camouflage jacket, worn loose over her shoulders.
The model of the moment completed her look with some smart accessories, including a pair of rock chic leather boots.
The 22-year-old beauty carried a smart black and white bag in one hand and wore her glossy locks pulled back in a loose ponytail.

Winnie recently spoke about being discovered by supermodel, entrepreneur and America's Next Top Model guru Tyra.
She revealed: 'When America's Next Top Model was casting for the new season I asked all my fans online to tag Tyra Banks so she could see my photos - and they did!'
'My little sister started a Facebook page for me and one of the producers from the show sent a message showing interest.
Wanna be on top? Winnie recently spoke about being discovered by supermodel, entrepreneur and America's Next Top Model guru Tyra
'Initially I didn't believe it but I followed through and ended up being on the show for season 21. After Tyra gave me that opportunity it was my time.'
Having been bullied at school for her vitiligo, Winnie added that she never expected to be the darling of the fashion industry.
The catwalk beauty recently told ELLE Canada she's not a fan of being branded a role model, as people shouldn't want to emulate others.
Winnie, who was rumoured to have enjoyed a fling with Lewis Hamilton last year, tells the publication: 'I feel like I am an inspiration. Thatâ€™s the word I prefer.
